annotationA: Mitochondrial trifunctional protein alpha subunit, isoform A; enoyl-CoA hydratase activity; long-chain-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA dehydrogenase activity; coenzyme binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: determination of adult lifespan; response to starvation; fatty acid beta-oxidation; wound healing
annotationB: 3-hydroxyisobutyryl-CoA hydrolase, mitochondrial; Hydrolyzes 3-hydroxyisobutyryl-CoA (HIBYL-CoA), a saline catabolite; Belongs to the enoyl-CoA hydratase/isomerase family
